## 7. Smart Contract (Chaincode) Design

The [EvotingContract](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/ドキュメント/chain/fabric-samples/evoting-chaincode/lib/evotingContract.js) is the heart of the system. It defines **four data types** (docTypes) stored on the blockchain ledger:

### 7.1 On-Chain Data Models

```mermaid
erDiagram
    CONSTITUENCY {
        string constituencyID PK
        string stateID
        string electionPhase
        string docType
    }
    VOTER {
        string epicHash PK
        string constituencyID FK
        string stateID
        string registeredMSP
        boolean voted
        string status
        string docType
    }
    CANDIDATE {
        string candidateID PK
        string name
        string party
        string constituencyID FK
        int voteCount
        string docType
    }
    VOTE {
        string voteID PK
        string candidateID FK
        string constituencyID FK
        string timestamp
        string docType
    }

    CONSTITUENCY ||--o{ VOTER : "registered in"
    CONSTITUENCY ||--o{ CANDIDATE : "contests in"
    CANDIDATE ||--o{ VOTE : "receives"
```

### 7.2 Chaincode Functions

| # | Function | Type | Access | Description |
|---|----------|------|--------|-------------|
| 1 | [createConstituency(id, stateID)](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/fabric-samples/evoting-chaincode/lib/evotingContract.js#36-58) | Write | Org1MSP | Creates a constituency with `electionPhase = "CREATED"` |
| 2 | [startElection(id)](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/evoting-frontend/src/services/api.js#22-25) | Write | Org1MSP | Sets `electionPhase = "VOTING"` |
| 3 | [endElection(id)](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/fabric-samples/evoting-chaincode/lib/evotingContract.js#78-96) | Write | Org1MSP | Sets `electionPhase = "CLOSED"` |
| 4 | [getConstituencyStatus(id)](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/fabric-samples/evoting-chaincode/lib/evotingContract.js#97-106) | Read | Any | Returns constituency details and current phase |
| 5 | [registerVoter(epic, constID, stateID)](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/evoting-frontend/src/services/api.js#35-39) | Write | Org1MSP | Hashes EPIC, validates constituency exists, stores voter |
| 6 | [registerCandidate(id, name, party, constID)](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/fabric-samples/evoting-chaincode/lib/evotingContract.js#155-193) | Write | Org1MSP | Validates constituency, stores candidate with `voteCount = 0` |
| 7 | [castVote(epic, candidateID)](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/fabric-samples/evoting-chaincode/lib/evotingContract.js#198-274) | Write | Any | Core voting logic with 5 validation checks |
| 8 | [getResults(constID)](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/evoting-frontend/src/services/api.js#53-56) | Read | Any | Scans all candidates in a constituency with vote counts |
| 9 | [getVotesByConstituency(constID)](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/evoting-frontend/src/services/api.js#57-60) | Read | Any | Returns all individual vote transaction records |
| 10 | [getVoterHistory(epic)](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/fabric-samples/evoting-chaincode/lib/evotingContract.js#345-375) | Read | Any | Returns full ledger history for a voter's key |

### 7.3 Vote Casting — Validation Pipeline

When [castVote()](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/fabric-samples/evoting-chaincode/lib/evotingContract.js#198-274) is invoked, the chaincode performs **5 sequential checks** before recording the vote:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["castVote(epicNumber, candidateID)"] --> B{"1. Voter exists?"}
    B -- No --> E1["❌ Voter does not exist"]
    B -- Yes --> C{"2. Voter status = ACTIVE?"}
    C -- No --> E2["❌ Voter not eligible"]
    C -- Yes --> D{"3. Already voted?"}
    D -- Yes --> E3["❌ Duplicate vote detected"]
    D -- No --> F{"4. Candidate exists &\nsame constituency?"}
    F -- No --> E4["❌ Cross-constituency\nvoting not allowed"]
    F -- Yes --> G{"5. Election phase\n= VOTING?"}
    G -- No --> E5["❌ Election not active"]
    G -- Yes --> H["✅ Record vote on ledger"]
    H --> I["Increment candidate.voteCount"]
    I --> J["Set voter.voted = true"]
```

