## 9. Frontend Application

The frontend is a **React SPA** bootstrapped with Create React App, using React Router v6 for navigation.

### 9.1 Page Map

| Route | Page Component | Access | Description |
|-------|---------------|--------|-------------|
| `/` | `PublicResults` | Public | Homepage — search constituency and view live results |
| `/vote` | `VoterBooth` | Public | Voter enters EPIC, selects candidate, casts vote |
| `/admin` | `AdminLogin` | Public | Admin login form (enter EC API key) |
| `/dashboard` | `AdminDashboard` | Protected | Admin overview |
| `/constituency` | `ConstituencyPage` | Protected | Create & manage constituencies, start/end elections |
| `/candidates` | `CandidatesPage` | Protected | Register candidates to constituencies |
| `/results` | `ResultsPage` | Protected | Admin results view |
| `/audit` | `AuditPage` | Protected | Query voter history and vote records |

### 9.2 Key Components

| Component | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| [Sidebar.jsx](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/evoting-frontend/src/components/Sidebar.jsx) | Navigation sidebar for admin pages |
| [CandidateCard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/evoting-frontend/src/components/CandidateCard.jsx) | Displays candidate info (name, party, vote count) |
| [StatusBadge.jsx](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/evoting-frontend/src/components/StatusBadge.jsx) | Visual badge for election phase (CREATED/VOTING/CLOSED) |

### 9.3 Auth Flow

The frontend uses **React Context** (`AuthContext`) to manage admin state:

1. Admin enters the EC API key on the login page.
2. On login, the key is stored in React state and injected into all Axios requests via [setAdminKey()](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/%E3%83%89%E3%82%AD%E3%83%A5%E3%83%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%83%88/chain/evoting-frontend/src/services/api.js#8-12).
3. Protected routes check `isAdmin` — if `false`, the user is redirected to `/admin`.
4. Logout clears the API key from Axios headers and resets state.

> [!NOTE]
> The API key is not stored in localStorage for security — it lives only in memory and is lost on page refresh.

