## 10. Data Flow & Sequence Diagrams

### 10.1 Vote Casting Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant V as Voter (Browser)
    participant API as Express Backend
    participant GW as Fabric Gateway
    participant P as Peer Node
    participant CC as EvotingContract
    participant L as Ledger

    V->>API: POST /api/voter/vote {epicNumber, candidateID}
    API->>GW: submit('castVote', epic, candidateID)
    GW->>P: submitTransaction (gRPC + TLS)
    P->>CC: invoke castVote()
    CC->>L: getState(epicHash) — check voter
    CC->>L: getState(candidateID) — check candidate
    CC->>L: getState(constituencyID) — check phase
    CC->>L: putState(voteID) — store vote record
    CC->>L: putState(candidateID) — increment count
    CC->>L: putState(epicHash) — mark voted=true
    CC-->>P: "Vote successfully cast"
    P-->>GW: Transaction committed
    GW-->>API: Response buffer
    API-->>V: { success: true, message: "Vote successfully cast" }
```

### 10.2 Admin Constituency Creation Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Admin (Browser)
    participant API as Express Backend
    participant Auth as Auth Middleware
    participant GW as Fabric Gateway
    participant CC as EvotingContract

    A->>API: POST /api/admin/constituency {id, stateID}<br/>(x-api-key header)
    API->>Auth: Check x-api-key
    Auth-->>API: ✅ Valid
    API->>GW: submit('createConstituency', id, stateID)
    GW->>CC: invoke createConstituency()
    CC->>CC: Check MSP = Org1MSP
    CC->>CC: Check constituency doesn't exist
    CC-->>GW: JSON constituency object
    GW-->>API: Parsed response
    API-->>A: { success: true, data: {...} }
```

---

## 11. Security Mechanisms

| Layer | Mechanism | Details |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| **Network** | TLS Encryption | All gRPC communication between SDK and peers uses TLS certificates |
| **Identity** | X.509 Certificates | Admin identity enrolled with Fabric CA; stored in local wallet |
| **API** | API Key Authentication | Admin routes require `x-api-key: EC-NATIONAL-2024` header |
| **Chaincode** | MSP Verification | Smart contract checks `ctx.clientIdentity.getMSPID() === "Org1MSP"` |
| **Voter Privacy** | SHA-256 Hashing | EPIC numbers are stored only as hashed values on the ledger |
| **Vote Integrity** | Duplicate Detection | Chaincode checks `voter.voted === true` before allowing a vote |
| **Constituency Isolation** | Cross-constituency Check | Voter's constituency must match candidate's constituency |
| **Election Phase** | State Machine | Votes only accepted when `electionPhase === "VOTING"` |
| **Immutability** | Blockchain | Once committed, ledger entries cannot be altered or deleted |
| **Audit** | History API | `getHistoryForKey()` provides full change log for any entity |

