## 12. Testing & Attack Simulations

The project includes a comprehensive **8-test attack & defense simulation suite** ([failureSimulations.js](file:///c:/Users/raksh/OneDrive/ドキュメント/chain/tests/failureSimulations.js)) that validates the system's resilience:

| Test # | Scenario | Expected Outcome | HTTP Code |
|--------|----------|-------------------|-----------|
| 1 | Valid Vote | ✅ Vote accepted | 200 |
| 2 | Duplicate Vote | ❌ Rejected — `DUPLICATE_VOTE` | 409 |
| 3 | Cross-Constituency Vote | ❌ Rejected — `VOTE_REJECTED` | 403 |
| 4 | Vote After Election Closed | ❌ Rejected — `ELECTION_INACTIVE` | 423 |
| 5 | Unregistered Voter | ❌ Rejected — voter doesn't exist | non-200 |
| 6 | Vote Before Election Starts | ❌ Rejected — election not active | non-200 |
| 7 | Unauthorized Admin Action | ❌ Rejected — no API key | 401 |
| 8 | Full Election Cycle + Results | ✅ Complete flow: vote → end → results | 200 |

**Run the tests:**
```bash
npm run simulate
```

